<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-02T01:06:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-30T14:29:00-05:00" n="591" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2410</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kandalaksha</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1918-08-02T02:06:00-04:00" notBefore="1918-07-31T00:00:00+04:31"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    August 2, 1918, 2.06 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <persName corresp="#p_PDC1">Poole</persName><note n="1" xml:id="d591fn1">
                                <persName corresp="#p_PDC1">DeWitt C. Poole</persName>, Consul at
                                Moscow.</note> reports having advised you departure of Diplomatic
                            Corps from Vologda and causes therefor. …<note n="2" xml:id="d591fn2">The detailed account of the trip, hopelessly garbled in
                                transmission, is omitted. Another account is given in the
                                Ambassador’s telegram No. 350, Aug. 4, <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                            </note> My intention and desire to remain in Russia. [Have not changed?]
                            my judgment as to our having ambassador here. My stay at Kandalaksha and
                            subsequent location will be influenced by developments. Plan to return
                            to Vologda when safe. [Will] advise the Department by cable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>